# Main body;A Web For All
Jun Ajk'amaya'l qichin qonojel


;As the Web expands to reach billions of new people and touch our lives in new ways, it has become an essential part of our individual growth and collective future. And that Web is what the Mozilla community has pledged to protect and promote: a platform providing opportunity, connectivity and inspiration for all.
Ri Ajk'amaya'l tajin nik'iyïr chi kikojol t'ijtäq k'ak'a' winaqi' chuqa' k'o nub'än pa k'ak'aslem chi jalajöj rub'anikil, xok qa jun nimaläj peraj richin qanimirisanik qayonil chuqa' qak'aslem ri chwa'q kab'ij. Ri Ajk'amaya'l ri', ja ri' tajin nuchajij chuqa' tajin nutaluj ri Mozilla moloj: jun nuk'uche'el ri yerusüj samaj, okem chuqa' kich'ab'enik konojel.


;We live our principles by making products, empowering communities, teaching skills and shaping environments in order to build the Internet the world needs.
K'o ri ruk'u'x qatzij rik'in kitz'ukik taq tikoj, niqaya' kuchuq'a' ri taq moloj, niqak'üt etamab'äl chuqa' tajin yeqanük' taq k'ojlib'äl richin ninuk' jun K'amaya'l, ri nik'atzin chi re ri ruwach'ulew.


;At this year’s Mozilla Summit, 2,000 people representing 90 countries and 114 languages gathered to develop a shared understanding of who we are and what we will accomplish together. Below is a sample of perspectives from leaders of the project.
Pa Mozilla Summit re juna' re', 2000 winaqi' kepe' pa 90 amaq'i' chuqa' 114 jalajöj taq ch'ab'äl, xkimöl ki' richin nikinük' xa xe jun na'oj pa ruwi' ri öj achike röj chuqa' achike yojtikïr niqab'än junam. Re jujun taq silowachib'äl nikik'üt jujun chi ke ri kitzub'al ri e ruk'amöl b'ey ri nimasamaj.


